INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('almalexia', 'Almalexia, revered as Almalexia the Lover and Ayem, was one of the three God-Kings of the Tribunal, a pantheon that included Vivec and Sotha Sil. Known for her compassion and protective nature, she earned titles such as "Healing Mother," "Lady of Mercy," and "Mother Morrowind" among the Dunmer. Residing in the temple city of Mournhold, Almalexia was deeply connected with House Indoril and was well-regarded for her approachability, often walking among her people. As a mortal, she was married to Lord Indoril Nerevar, the First Councilor of Resdayn, and later became the Consort of Vivec after her husband''s death in the Battle of Red Mountain.

Following Nerevar''s demise, Almalexia and the other Tribunal members swore an oath to never exploit the divine power of the Heart of Lorkhan, a promise they eventually broke to achieve godhood. This transformation not only changed the Chimer into the Dunmer but also established the Tribunal as immortal protectors of the Dunmer people. However, the truth of their ascendance was obscured, portrayed instead as a result of their virtues and wisdom. Over time, Almalexia''s powers waned, particularly during her battles against Dagoth Ur. Eventually, she succumbed to madness, culminating in the murder of Sotha Sil and her own death in a failed attempt to eliminate the Nerevarine in 3E 427.', '''3e'':222B ''427'':223B ''achiev'':142B ''after'':101B ''against'':194B ''almalexi'':1A,2B,5B,59B,116B,186B ''also'':155B ''among'':49B,76B ''an'':123B ''and'':8B,26B,33B,46B,66B,94B,117B,182B,209B ''approachability'':73B ''as'':4B,40B,79B,159B,176B ''ascendanc'':171B ''attempt'':216B ''ayem'':9B ''battl'':108B,193B ''becam'':96B ''brok'':140B ''but'':154B ''chang'':148B ''chim'':150B ''city'':56B ''compassion'':32B ''connect'':62B ''consort'':98B ''councilor'':91B ''culminating'':202B ''dagoth'':195B ''death'':105B,212B ''deeply'':61B ''demis'':115B ''divin'':129B ''dunm'':51B,153B,164B ''during'':191B ''earn'':37B ''eliminat'':218B ''establish'':156B ''eventually'':139B,197B ''exploit'':127B ''fail'':215B ''first'':90B ''following'':112B ''for'':30B,71B ''god'':16B ''god-kings'':15B ''godhood'':143B ''healing'':41B ''heart'':133B ''her'':31B,72B,77B,102B,192B,210B ''hous'':64B ''howev'':166B ''husband'':103B ''immortal'':160B ''in'':53B,106B,203B,213B,221B ''includ'':24B ''indoril'':65B,87B ''inste'':175B ''into'':151B ''kings'':17B ''known'':29B ''lady'':43B ''lat'':95B ''lord'':86B ''lorkh'':135B ''lov'':7B ''madness'':201B ''marri'':84B ''members'':121B ''mercy'':45B ''morrowind'':48B ''mortal'':81B ''moth'':42B,47B ''mountain'':111B ''mournhold'':58B ''murd'':205B ''natur'':35