INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('mythic_dawn', 'The Mythic Dawn, a secretive and zealous cult, worshiped Mehrunes Dagon, the Daedric Prince of Destruction. Founded centuries before its rise to infamy, the cult became widely known for its pivotal role in the Oblivion Crisis of 3E 433. Under the leadership of the enigmatic and "mad" Mankar Camoran, the cult orchestrated the assassination of Emperor Uriel Septim VII and his heirs, collapsing the divine barrier known as the Dragonfires and enabling Dagon’s forces to invade Tamriel. With sleeper agents scattered throughout the Empire and their main shrine hidden near Lake Arrius, the cult thrived in secrecy. Their ultimate defeat came through the intervention of the Hero of Kvatch, who dismantled the cult, killed Camoran and his children, and banished Mehrunes Dagon from Nirn, thus ending the Third Era.

In the centuries following their downfall, remnants of the Mythic Dawn persisted in legend and occasional resurgence. By 4E 201, the cult saw a partial revival through individuals like Silus Vesuius, who established a museum in Dawnstar to preserve their history, and Vonos, a high priest drawn to an ancient Oblivion Gate in the Velothi Mountains.', '''201'':152B ''3e'':40B ''433'':41B ''4e'':151B ''agents'':83B ''an'':181B ''ancient'':182B ''and'':8B,48B,62B,73B,88B,119B,122B,147B,174B ''arrius'':95B ''as'':70B ''assassination'':56B ''banish'':123B ''barri'':68B ''becam'':28B ''befor'':21B ''by'':150B ''cam'':104B ''camor'':51B,118B ''centuri'':20B,135B ''childr'':121B ''collapsing'':65B ''crisis'':38B ''cult'':10B,27B,53B,97B,116B,154B ''daedric'':15B ''dagon'':13B,75B,125B ''dawn'':2A,5B,143B ''dawnst'':169B ''defeat'':103B ''destruction'':18B ''dismantl'':114B ''divin'':67B ''downfall'':138B ''dragonfir'':72B ''drawn'':179B ''emperor'':58B ''empir'':87B ''enabling'':74B ''ending'':129B ''enigmatic'':47B ''establish'':165B ''following'':136B ''for'':31B ''forc'':77B ''found'':19B ''from'':126B ''gat'':184B ''heirs'':64B ''her'':110B ''hidd'':92B ''high'':177B ''his'':63B,120B ''history'':173B ''in'':35B,99B,133B,145B,168B,185B ''individuals'':160B ''infamy'':25B ''intervention'':107B ''invad'':79B ''its'':22B,32B ''kill'':117B ''known'':30B,69B ''kvatch'':112B ''lak'':94B ''leadership'':44B ''legend'':146B ''lik'':161B ''mad'':49B ''main'':90B ''mank'':50B ''mehrun'':12B,124B ''mountains'':188B ''museum'':167B ''mythic'':1A,4B,142B ''near'':93B ''nirn'':127B ''oblivion'':37B,183B ''occasional'':148B ''of'':17B,39B,45B,57B,108B,111B,140B ''orchestrat'':54B ''partial'':157B ''persist'':144B ''pivotal'':33B ''preserv'':171B ''priest'':178B ''princ'':16B ''remnants'':139B ''resurgenc'':149B ''revival'':158B ''ris'':23B ''rol'':34B ''s'':76B ''saw'':155B ''scatter'':84B ''secrecy'':100B ''secretiv'':7B ''septim'':60B ''shrin'':91B ''silus'':162B ''sleep'':82B ''tamriel