INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('alessian_slave_rebellion', 'The Alessian Slave Rebellion was a landmark conflict in Tamrielic history, spanning from 1E 242 to 1E 243. Led by the Slave-Queen Alessia, the rebellion marked the liberation of the Nedic people from their Ayleid overlords, who had dominated Cyrodiil through a brutal regime of Daedra worship, enslavement, and ritual cruelty. With divine guidance from the Eight Divines and the aid of key allies like Pelinal Whitestrake and Morihaus, Alessia united human slaves and sympathetic Ayleid factions in a desperate uprising. The rebellion culminated in the Siege of White-Gold Tower, where Pelinal slew the demigod Umaril the Unfeathered but fell in battle. This victory dismantled the Ayleid Empire and laid the foundation for the Alessian Empire, ushering in the dominance of men over mer in Cyrodiil.

The rebellion not only freed the Nedic slaves but also began the Ayleids'' gradual decline. Many Daedra-worshipping Ayleids fled to Valenwood and High Rock, while their remaining city-states either integrated into the new Empire as vassals or were annihilated by the Alessian forces. The rebellion’s aftermath saw Alessia crowned as the first Empress of Cyrodiil, the establishment of the Amulet of Kings to protect Mundus from Oblivion, and the rise of the Imperial Pantheon, blending elements of Nordic and Elven faiths. However, centuries later, the rise of the Alessian Order would erase much of the Ayleid presence from Cyrodiil, ensuring the once-mighty Heartland High Elves faded into obscurity. The rebellion marked a critical turning point in Tamriel’s history, redefining its religious, cultural, and political landscape.', '''1e'':17B,20B ''242'':18B ''243'':21B ''aftermath'':184B ''aid'':66B ''alessi'':1A,5B,28B,75B,122B,179B,186B,227B ''alli'':69B ''also'':143B ''amulet'':198B ''and'':54B,64B,73B,79B,116B,157B,206B,217B,264B ''annihilat'':176B ''as'':172B,188B ''ayle'':40B,81B,114B,234B ''ayleids'':146B,153B ''battl'':109B ''beg'':144B ''blending'':213B ''brutal'':48B ''but'':106B,142B ''by'':23B,177B ''centuri'':221B ''city'':164B ''city-stat'':163B ''conflict'':11B ''critical'':253B ''crown'':187B ''cruelty'':56B ''culminat'':89B ''cultural'':263B ''cyrodiil'':45B,133B,193B,237B ''daedr'':51B,151B ''daedra-worshipping'':150B ''declin'':148B ''demigod'':102B ''desperat'':85B ''dismantl'':112B ''divin'':58B,63B ''dominanc'':127B ''dominat'':44B ''eight'':62B ''eith'':166B ''elements'':214B ''elven'':218B ''elves'':245B ''empir'':115B,123B,171B ''empress'':191B ''enslavement'':53B ''ensuring'':238B ''eras'':230B ''establishment'':195B ''factions'':82B ''fad'':246B ''faiths'':219B ''fell'':107B ''first'':190B ''fled'':154B ''for'':120B ''forc'':180B ''foundation'':119B ''fre'':138B ''from'':16B,38B,60B,204B,236B ''gold'':96B ''gradual'':147B ''guidanc'':59B ''had'':4