INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('a_children''s_anuad', 'A Children''s Anuad: The Anuad Paraphrased, written by an unknown author, is a simplified recounting of the Anuad creation myth, describing the origins of Nirn and the interplay of cosmic forces. The myth begins with Anu and Padomay, primordial brothers whose interactions in the Void created Nir, who gave birth to Creation after a tragic conflict. Anu and Padomay clashed over Nir, leading to her death and the shattering of the twelve worlds of Creation. In the aftermath, Anu reformed the remnants into Nirn, only to be mortally wounded by Padomay, and both were cast outside Time. Their mingled blood gave rise to the Aedra, while Padomay’s blood formed the Daedra, and Anu’s blood became the stars.

The myth continues with the descendants of Creation’s survivors, the Ehlnofey and Hist, who shaped the world through war and migration. The Old Ehlnofey became the ancestors of Mer, giving rise to elves like the Altmer, Bosmer, and Dunmer in Tamriel, while the Wandering Ehlnofey spread across other continents to become Men, such as the Nords and Redguards. The great Ehlnofey war reshaped Nirn, forming its continents and oceans, while the Hist were largely destroyed, surviving only in Black Marsh. The tale ends with the Nords returning to Tamriel under Ysgramor’s leadership, marking the end of the Mythic Era and the start of recorded history.', '''across'':172B ''aedr'':110B ''after'':58B ''aftermath'':83B ''altmer'':161B ''an'':14B ''ancestors'':152B ''and'':31B,42B,63B,72B,97B,118B,137B,145B,163B,182B,193B,226B ''anu'':4A,8B,10B,23B,41B,62B,84B,119B ''as'':179B ''author'':16B ''be'':92B ''becam'':122B,150B ''becom'':176B ''begins'':39B ''birth'':55B ''black'':204B ''blood'':105B,114B,121B ''bosm'':162B ''both'':98B ''brothers'':45B ''by'':13B,95B ''cast'':100B ''childr'':2A,6B ''clash'':65B ''conflict'':61B ''continents'':174B,192B ''continu'':127B ''cosmic'':35B ''creat'':51B ''creation'':24B,57B,80B,132B ''daedr'':117B ''death'':71B ''descendants'':130B ''describing'':26B ''destroy'':200B ''dunm'':164B ''ehlnofey'':136B,149B,170B,186B ''elves'':158B ''end'':221B ''ends'':208B ''forc'':36B ''form'':115B ''forming'':190B ''gav'':54B,106B ''giving'':155B ''great'':185B ''her'':70B ''hist'':138B,197B ''history'':231B ''in'':48B,81B,165B,203B ''interactions'':47B ''interplay'':33B ''into'':88B ''is'':17B ''its'':191B ''largely'':199B ''leadership'':218B ''leading'':68B ''lik'':159B ''marking'':219B ''marsh'':205B ''men'':177B ''mer'':154B ''migration'':146B ''mingl'':104B ''mortally'':93B ''myth'':25B,38B,126B ''mythic'':224B ''nir'':52B,67B ''nirn'':30B,89B,189B ''nords'':181B,211B ''oceans'':194B ''of'':21B,29B,34B,75B,79B,131B,153B,222B,229B ''old'':148B ''only'':9