INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('ruptga', 'Ruptga, known as Tall Papa, is the chief deity of the Yokudan and Redguard pantheon and a central figure in their mythology. As the first spirit to escape the endless cycles of creation and destruction brought by Satakal, the Worldskin, Ruptga is revered as the god who charted the path to the Far Shores, the sanctuary beyond the cycles of hunger. Using his immense height, he placed the stars in the sky to serve as a guiding map for other spirits seeking escape. However, Ruptga’s role is not only that of a savior; he also acted as a judge, punishing Sep, the Second Serpent, for deceiving spirits into inhabiting the mortal world, which left them vulnerable to hunger and mortality. The void left by Sep’s death remains as a hungry force chasing the stars, a haunting reminder of his trickery.

