INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('windhelm', 'Windhelm is a major city in northeastern Skyrim, located near the Dunmeth Pass to Morrowind and serving as the capital of Eastmarch. Situated near the northern coast, the city experiences extreme cold and frequent blizzards. Windhelm is ruled by Jarl Ulfric Stormcloak, the leader of the Stormcloak Rebellion, who resides in the Palace of the Kings. Known for its open defiance of the Imperial ban on Talos worship, Windhelm features a prominent Temple of Talos. However, the city is also infamous for its anti-foreigner sentiment, particularly toward its sizable population of Dark Elves, who live in the cramped Gray Quarter, and Argonians, who are confined to the docks outside the city walls.

