INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('cyrodiil', '
Cyrodiil, the heartland of Tamriel and home to the Imperials, serves as the seat of the Empire and the location of its capital, the Imperial City. Dominated by the iconic White-Gold Tower, Cyrodiil is central to Tamriel''s history and culture. Though initially described as a jungle, its climate is temperate, possibly altered by Emperor Tiber Septim. The province''s early history is marked by the rule of the Ayleids, who enslaved the native Nedic people. The rebellion led by Alessia in 1E 242 ended Ayleid dominance, establishing the Alessian Empire and shaping Cyrodiil into a center of human governance and culture. The Alessians expanded westward, influenced by the prophet Marukh''s teachings, which codified much of Tamriel’s religion.

