INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('balmora', '
Balmora, meaning "Stonewood" or "Stoneforest" in the Dark Elvish tongue, was a prominent city in Vvardenfell, serving as the seat of House Hlaalu''s power and the second-largest settlement after Vivec City. Located in the river valley of the West Gash, on the banks of the Odai River, the city was divided into three key districts: the bustling Commercial District, the residential Labor Town, and the affluent High Town. Known for its strategic trade location and Hlaalu-style architecture, Balmora played a vital role in the economic and political landscape of Vvardenfell, acting as a gateway between the region''s rugged landscapes and fertile coastlines. Significant landmarks included the Hlaalu Council Manor, the Tribunal Temple, and the Moonmoth Imperial Legion Fort.

