INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('seyda_neen', 'Seyda Neen, often called the "Gateway to Vvardenfell," was a small yet significant port village in the southern Bitter Coast region, renowned for its lighthouse, the Grand Pharos. Originating from a House Hlaalu fleet''s ill-fated voyage to seek the "face of Veloth," the settlement was constructed from the remnants of the destroyed fleet. Over time, Seyda Neen became a vital stop for Imperial travelers heading to Vvardenfell, with its port managed by House Hlaalu and protected by the Imperial Legion. The village featured Imperial-style architecture built by the Gold Coast Trading Company, a Census and Excise Office for processing visitors, and a silt strider port providing connections to key destinations like Vivec and Balmora.

By the late Third Era, Seyda Neen served as a bustling hub for maritime activity and trade, though its surrounding swamplands earned it the nickname "Swamp Fever Capital of the World." Wildlife such as cliff racers, slaughterfish, and scribs populated the area, and Imperial cutters patrolled the waters to combat smuggling. However, Seyda Neen''s fate remains uncertain following the Red Year (4E 5) and the catastrophic eruption of Red Mountain, which devastated Vvardenfell and surrounding regions. Given its proximity to Vivec City, which bore the brunt of the disaster, it is unlikely Seyda Neen survived intact, leaving its legacy shrouded in mystery.', '''4e'':184B ''5'':185B ''activity'':136B ''and'':80B,102B,108B,120B,137B,159B,164B,186B,196B ''architectur'':92B ''are'':163B ''as'':130B,155B ''balmor'':121B ''becam'':63B ''bitt'':21B ''bor'':206B ''brunt'':208B ''built'':93B ''bustling'':132B ''by'':77B,82B,94B,122B ''call'':6B ''capital'':149B ''catastrophic'':188B ''census'':101B ''city'':204B ''cliff'':156B ''coast'':22B,97B ''combat'':171B ''company'':99B ''connections'':114B ''construct'':51B ''cutters'':166B ''destinations'':117B ''destroy'':57B ''devastat'':194B ''disast'':211B ''earn'':143B ''eruption'':189B ''excis'':103B ''fac'':45B ''fat'':40B,177B ''featur'':88B ''fev'':148B ''fleet'':36B,58B ''following'':180B ''for'':25B,67B,105B,134B ''from'':32B,52B ''gateway'':8B ''giv'':199B ''gold'':96B ''grand'':29B ''heading'':70B ''hlaalu'':35B,79B ''hous'':34B,78B ''howev'':173B ''hub'':133B ''ill'':39B ''ill-fat'':38B ''imperial'':68B,84B,90B,165B ''imperial-styl'':89B ''in'':18B,223B ''intact'':218B ''is'':213B ''it'':144B,212B ''its'':26B,74B,140B,200B,220B ''key'':116B ''lat'':124B ''leaving'':219B ''legacy'':221B ''legion'':85B ''lighthous'':27B ''lik'':118B ''manag'':76B ''maritim'':135B ''mountain'':192B ''mystery'':224B ''neen'':2A,4B,62B,128B,175B,216B ''nicknam'':146B ''of'':46B,55B,150B,190B,209B ''offic'':104B ''often'':5B ''originating'':31B ''ov