INSERT INTO public.oghma VALUES ('marbruk', 'Marbruk, located in the forested region of Greenshade in Valenwood, serves as a significant historical and cultural site. Originally settled by an Ayleid clan following the Alessian Slave Rebellion, the city evolved into a Bosmer settlement before being transformed into a fortified bastion by the Aldmeri Dominion in 2E 580. Built to defend Greenshade from external threats, its construction showcased modern Altmeri architecture, blending imported materials to respect the Green Pact while constructing atop ancient Ayleid ruins. The city became a symbol of Dominion unity but also sparked cultural tensions, as the Altmer enforced restrictions on traditional Bosmer practices. Marbruk''s Mages Guild vault housed priceless artifacts, including the Staff of Magnus, which played a central role in a Veiled Heritance attack led by the lich Prince Naemon. The Dominion, with the Vestige''s aid, repelled the undead assault and secured the city.

Throughout its history, Marbruk changed hands multiple times, reflecting the shifting political landscape of Valenwood. It was annexed by the Second Aldmeri Dominion during a Camoran civil war in 2E 830 but fell to Tiber Septim''s forces following his use of the Numidium in 2E 896, becoming part of the Third Empire. By the Third Era, the city had diminished to a small settlement known as Marbruk Field, ruled by Lord Palinis and enduring periods of rebellion and strife, including the Camoran Usurper Rebellion and the Oblivion Crisis. In 4E 29, a Thalmor-backed coup reclaimed Valenwood for the Aldmeri Dominion, marking Marbruk''s third incorporation into the Dominion. Despite its turbulent past, Marbruk remains a testament to the layered history and cultural dynamics of Valenwood.', '''29'':236B ''2e'':50B,174B,190B ''4e'':235B ''580'':51B ''830'':175B ''896'':191B ''aid'':136B ''aldmeri'':47B,166B,246B ''alessi'':28B ''also'':88B ''altmer'':94B ''altmeri'':63B ''an'':23B ''ancient'':76B ''and'':17B,141B,218B,223B,230B,268B ''annex'':162B ''architectur'':64B ''artifacts'':108B ''as'':13B,92B,211B ''assault'':140B ''atop'':75B ''attack'':123B ''ayle'':24B,77B ''back'':240B ''bastion'':44B ''becam'':81B ''becoming'':192B ''befor'':38B ''being'':39B ''blending'':65B ''bosm'':36B,99B ''built'':52B ''but'':87B,176B ''by'':22B,45B,125B,163B,198B,215B ''camor'':170B,227B ''central'':117B ''chang'':149B ''city'':32B,80B,144B,203B ''civil'':171B ''clan'':25B ''constructing'':74B ''construction'':60B ''coup'':241B ''crisis'':233B ''cultural'':18B,90B,269B ''defend'':54B ''despit'':256B ''diminish'':205B ''dominion'':48B,85B,131B,167B,247B,255B ''during'':168B ''dynamics'':270B ''empir'':197B ''enduring'':219B ''enforc'':95B ''evolv'':33B ''external'':57B ''fell'':177B ''field'':213B ''following'':26B,183B ''for'':244B ''forc'':182B ''forest'':6B ''fortifi'':43B ''from'':56B ''gre'':71B ''greenshad'':9B,55B ''guild'':104B ''had'':204B ''hands'':150B ''heritanc'':122B ''his'':184